input.description:
Create a hook that collects `contextMenu: true` commands from the scope chain and shows a native popup via Rust.

Since only one context menu can be open at a time, use a module-level pending handlers map.

```ts
// lib/context-menu.ts
const pendingHandlers = new Map<string, CommandDef>();

export function useContextMenu(): (e: React.MouseEvent) => void {
  const commands = useAvailableCommands();
  const contextCommands = commands.filter(c => c.command.contextMenu);

  return (e: React.MouseEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    e.stopPropagation();
    pendingHandlers.clear();
    const items = contextCommands.map(c => {
      pendingHandlers.set(c.command.id, c.command);
      return { id: c.command.id, name: c.command.name };
    });
    invoke("show_context_menu", { items });
  };
}
```

Global listener (in AppShell or a dedicated component) listens for `context-menu-command` event and dispatches from pendingHandlers.

- [ ] Create lib/context-menu.ts with useContextMenu hook
- [ ] Add module-level pendingHandlers map
- [ ] Add global listener for `context-menu-command` in AppShell
- [ ] Add tests
- [ ] Run tests

